\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Title:
\b0  Dimensionality reduction - Concepts and applications in scRNA-seq and DNA microscopy\
\
\

\b Abstract
\b0 \
Various forms of dimensionality reduction are used throughout data analysis pipelines applied to sequencing data. In this talk I first summarise the main concepts in dimensionality reduction, and clarify what certain methods were designed for, and in what situations should they be applied. I will shortly describe the popular linear ( PCA, MDS ) and non-linear ( t-SNE, isomap, LLE ) dimensionality reduction methods, and discuss their suitability for noise reduction, visualisation and manifold discovery. Finally, I explore applications for scRNA-seq data [1] and in the context of DNA microscopy [2].\
